			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OK, Myth busting time.
<br />

<br />
AFAIK, it IS possible to have a delay lower than 10. 
<br />

<br />
Here's how the confusion came about:
<br />

<br />
Now, a delay of 10 is one swing a second. Certain popular parsing programs sample every one second, so if you swung twice in that second (delay 5) it'd only pick up the one swing and report a delay of 10.
<br />

<br />
This info was plucked from another haste thread on this board.<br />_________________<br /><image src="http://www.toogeektolive.org.uk/images/surgecrit.jpg"><BR>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=660181" target="_blank" class="postlink">Surgen Sureglade - 55 Outrider of Tunare</a><BR><a href="http://www.lastfrag.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">&lt;After Image&gt;</a><BR>Vazaelle Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
