				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Elgor01 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Hi all,
<br />
 Back when we were talking about this issue on Everlore, Verant (Remember them) flat said there is a min delay you cant go below. We were never able to find out what it was but in 1999 or 2000 they did say there was a min delay. Also, most programs do sample at 1 second intervals and I have never seen my Ranger swing faster then 1 time per second.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
If you parse a fast weapon at various haste percentages, the DPS numbers should convince you that there's no min delay. The Mosscovered Twig--at exactly 10 delay--is a perfect example. I can't find any of the old threads about it, but the DPS with max haste was almost twice what it was with no haste. If swinging faster wasn't generating the extra DPS, what was causing it?
<br />

<br />
The reason parsing programs sample every whole second is because the game log doesn't show any series of events in a shorter interval than that.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~ytrill/ytrill8.jpg" border="0" />
